headline: Mission Produce's Momentum Fades in August: Buy Now or Stay Cautious?
summary: AVO's August momentum slows as margin pressures, supply risks and rising costs temper optimism despite record revenues and strong fundamentals.

headline: US Farmers Are Pulling Back on Spending in Threat to Rural Economy
summary: The contrast couldn’t be greater with the sentiment among attendees as low crop prices and trade tariffs squeeze the agricultural sector.  The market for American crops is getting “pretty nasty,” said Scott Metzger, who drove more than 300 miles (482 kilometers) to attend.  America’s farmers are expecting bumper crops this fall, but they’ve got little idea of where all the supplies will go.
